3. How do you display predicted vs actual values?

Industry-standard scatter plot with perfect prediction diagonal:

python
import plotly.express as px

# Production predicted vs actual plot
fig = px.scatter(x=y_pred, y=y_true,
                labels={'x': 'Predicted', 'y': 'Actual'},
                trendline='ols',  # Best fit line
                title="Model Calibration: Predicted vs Actual Values")

# Add perfect prediction line (45° diagonal)
max_val = max(y_pred.max(), y_true.max())
fig.add_shape(type="line", x0=0, y0=0, x1=max_val, y1=max_val,
              line=dict(color="red", dash="dash"))
st.plotly_chart(fig)

Diagnostic Patterns:

text
✅ Points cluster around diagonal → Well-calibrated
⚠️  Points above diagonal → Systematic under-prediction
❌ Points scatter randomly → Poor model fit



4. What is st.metric() used for in ML dashboards?

st.metric() creates executive-friendly KPI cards with delta indicators:

python
col1, col2, col3, col4 = st.columns(4)

col1.metric("R² Score", 0.82, "+0.05")           # Primary metric
