5. How can errors be visualized using Streamlit charts?

Comprehensive error analysis dashboard:

python
# === RESIDUALS ANALYSIS (Production template) ===
st.subheader("🔍 Error Analysis")

col1, col2 = st.columns(2)

# 1. RESIDUALS vs PREDICTIONS (Heteroscedasticity test)
with col1:
    residuals = y_true - y_pred
    fig1 = px.scatter(x=y_pred, y=residuals,
                     labels={'x':'Predicted', 'y':'Residuals (₹L)'},
                     trendline='lowess',
                     title="Residuals Pattern (Should be random)")
    st.plotly_chart(fig1)

# 2. ERROR DISTRIBUTION (Outlier detection)
with col2:
    fig2 = px.histogram(x=residuals/1e5, nbins=50,
                       labels={'x':'Error (₹L)'},
                       title="Error Distribution (Should be normal)")
    st.plotly_chart(fig2)

# 3. ERROR BY FEATURE (Bias detection)
error_by_feature = df_test.assign(error=residuals/1e5)
fig3 = px.box(error_by_feature, x='department', y='error',
             title="Errors by Department")
st.plotly_chart(fig3)

Error Pattern Diagnosis:

| Visual Pattern     | Problem                 | Fix                  |
| ------------------ | ----------------------- | -------------------- |
| Funnel shape       | Heteroscedasticity      | Log-transform target |
| Step pattern       | Categorical bias        | One-hot encoding     |
| Skewed errors      | Non-linear relationship | Polynomial features  |
| Clustered outliers | Data quality            | Winsorize/remove     |

